ight: 12px; width: 16px; transform: translateY(-4px);"></div><div style=" width: 0; height: 0; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-left: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(-4px) translateX(8px);"></div></div></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 24px;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 224px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 144px;"></div></div><p></p><p style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DFcmBLnCd-s/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">特色艺术家联盟（@featustrusatistscaalition）共享的帖子</a></p></div></blockquote><p><script async src="//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script></p><p>他说：“我们无法预测它的外观。” “我们需要知道它将如何分发，以及它将如何吸引艺术家，尤其是如果我们有艺术家付款。这应该是征税而不是艺术家捐赠系统。我希望看到的是，在所有演出中的所有演出中都非常迅速地付出了1英镑的毯子征费，这笔资金将用于现场信托基金会，并在平等的场地和艺术家之间分发，其中一些钱也将用于发起人。”</p><p>他继续说：“老实说，我认为我们没有通过怀旧的场所来解决这个问题，我说，作为对场地怀旧的人。人们挂断的是，一旦您对这次对话深入了解，我们试图解决的问题就会被遗忘。</p><p> “我们要解决的问题是：游览价格昂贵，外出价格昂贵，如果人们将票价推高以支付成本，那么它的成本高分，而且球迷们的口袋里没有钱。”</p><p> FAC首席执行官还说：“年轻的球迷发现很难离开并看到他们喜欢的艺术家”，“目前英国艺术家对录制音乐的需求很高，但他们没有现场直播” 。 FAC遇到了艺术家，每月1000万个听众仍然负担不起巡回演出。</p><p>他继续说：“最终，这就是问题：我们必须维持供应链和观众的增长。” “我们已经失去了大流行期间隐藏的那一代人，我们需要重新点燃新的观众和现场音乐之间的联系，我们需要使新艺术家能够走出路。”</p><p>马丁指出<a href="https://newsroom.spotify.com/2024-12-04/top-songs-artists-podcasts-audiobooks-albums-trends-2024/">Spotify是2024年全球最流行的艺术家</a>，他说，英国的名字越来越不足，这表明人才管道已经遭受了苦难，而不是缺乏才华。</p><p>他承认：“我并不是说这是世界末日，这是可以解决的，但这应该是英国音乐行业的金丝雀。” “整个生态系统能够共同刺激活动？大型竞技场和发起人需要具有远见。您希望他们这样。</p><p> “我们都应该非常担心。在过去七年中，英国在全球音乐市场中的份额已从17％降至10％。去年，有多少英国艺术家在整个官方排行榜上排名最高？这些应该是该行业的危险信号。如果您希望场地做得好，请确保您在其中有表演，并且正在激发新的受众。您希望发起人做得好吗？通过允许艺术家建立新的粉丝群来确保有需求。”</p><p>马丁最终说，英国需要紧急解决围绕<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-sales-hit-20-year-high-but-beneath-the-surface-uk-artists-earn-far-below-average-salaries-3827139">流媒体</a>，基层征税， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brexit-touring-europe-strangling-talent-carnets-visa-merch-crew-government-response-summer-2022-3288735">英国脱欧对巡回演出的影响</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/elton-john-backs-paul-mccartney-over-proposed-ai-copyright-law-this-will-dilute-and-threaten-young-artists-earnings-3832051">AI法规的</a>影响。</p><p>他补充说：“现在，我们需要增长和轻松获胜。” “我认为英国对其潜力的成就却极大地不足。我知道那里的需求以及我们拥有的艺术家的质量。坦率地说，任何说“不再有好音乐”的人都充满了狗屎。那里有很多优秀的音乐，它很难削减，而且在英国的支持下也不是很好。” </p><figure id="attachment_3554574" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3554574" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3554574" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story.jpg" alt="节日人群" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Nozstockfestival-story-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3554574" class="wp-caption-text"> Nozstock节的人群。学分：卢克·布伦南/盖蒂</figcaption></figure><p>约翰·罗斯特朗（John Rostron）是独立节日协会的首席执行官。去年，在<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-festivals-cancelled-postponed-2023-2024-money-covid-weather-3577792">大量取消和推迟</a>后，他们看到了78个节日的失败。他告诉<em>NME</em> ：“这是2023年的数字两倍，这意味着自大流行以来的200多个节日已经消失。”</p><p> “这是丢失事件的记录中最糟糕的数字，其中两个都是独立的节日。英国的大多数节日都是独立的，它们是最有风险的节日，因为它们没有相同的跨国公司可能会经历有问题的时代。”</p><p>他继续说：“现在，在2025年，利润率如此之大，这些事件的现金流动是如此艰难，供应链条款是他们有史以来最艰难的，从售票公司促进资金的货币要谨慎得多。现在，您已经有成功的活动将卖得很好或卖光并会赚钱，但是他们赚到的钱是如此微不足道，以至于不再值得全年举办该活动的压力，因为任何错误余地 - 不好天气，一笔巨大的水钱，互联网在酒吧里辍学了几个小时 - 可能是赚钱或亏损之间的区别。” </p><figure id="attachment_3808599" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3808599" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3808599" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/Kendal-Calling-2024.-CREDIT_-Tom-Martin-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3808599" class="wp-caption-text">肯德尔致电2024。信用：汤姆·马丁</figcaption></figure><p>Rostron补充说，节日仍然感觉到Covid对新受众再生的影响的尾声 - 创造了一个“压力锅”环境，并在英国脱欧，巡回演出和基础设施成本的影响下。</p><p>至于征税，罗斯特朗说，AIF“参与其中，并就需要这笔钱支持整个生态系统（包括基层节日）进行了很好的对话。”</p><p>他说：“如果您只是整理场地，如果节日崩溃，那就不好了。” “这都是生态系统的一部分。 We&#39;ve got programmes that we&#39;re setting up for when the levy arrives, but there won&#39;t be any meaningful contributions from that until autumn 2026 at the earliest.</p><p> However, even with the levy in place, UK festivals would not see any real benefit until 2027 due to their seasonal nature.</p><p> “The levy is agreed on fixed shows over 5,000 capacity on a voluntary basis, but most of the big shows for this year have been announced,” said Rostron. “There might be the odd one announced with the levy added, but we&#39;re not going to see many until next year and the money won&#39;t come in until the show is reconciled – which will be autumn 2026 before our festivals return in summer 2027。</p><p> “The problem we have now is in that gap between now and next autumn, so we&#39;ve got to get through two more seasons with no support. We&#39;ve been involved in the levy conversations and it&#39;s been understood and accepted that this should benefit venues, artists, promoters and festivals – but the question is now what can be done to support us in the next two years?</p><p> “I told a minister that we lost 70 festivals last year and we&#39;re not going to be OK in just hoping for 2026; we need government support to help with that gap. It&#39;s very positive and welcome, but it&#39;s also not going to be enough. We can&#39;t lose another 114 events.”</p><p> In the meantime, Rostron said that the best way for music fans to support festivals was to put a deposit down on a ticket to an event to secure them going ahead, and to “write to their MP and say, &#39;I&#39;m worried about my favourite festival – what are you doing about it?&#39;”</p><p> “We&#39;ve done everything that we can in this world, it&#39;s just tumultuous circumstances around us,” he ended. “We need a VAT reduction or some temporary fiscal support. It&#39;s now up to the government to change that for the better. We don&#39;t need a lot.” </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/DC1bpVpMtay/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0;